SENT.plain: Among 216 examined patients 96 demonstrated clinical symptoms which neither fitted into the classical alternating syndromes nor into the syndrome of Foit-Gilleman
It should be held in mind that the magistral vessels (vertebral arteries) and the minor vessels of the stem are involved in the pathogenesis of "nondifferentiated" "multiple level" syndromes
Their anatomo-physiological condition determines the final realization of the pathological process, its anatomical localization and extensiveness
